Latinos still slurred between apartments as human pack animals loaded with around 50 ironed t-shirts hanging on a yoke-like pole on their shoulders.
Office workers are still waiting on their breakfast bar at food stands on the sidewalks and it is still impossible to get a yellow taxi on a day of the week between 4 pm and 7 pm.
It didn’t feel like a crisis at all until I decided to open a new savings account on Thursday afternoon due to all the world’s downfall.
