Normal New Yorkers have acquired a fluent financial Latin in the last few weeks.
A woman who was on the phone in my Chinese tribal supermarket, with so much familiarity, referred to Lehman Brothers, the bank that went bankrupt, and their slender-looking CEO Dick Fuld as if she were blaming a lazy colleague.
