Drivers who may become relapsed due to the alcohol level will have to install the 'Alcolock'.
The authority orders that the driver, who had three official penalties for alcohol levels, installs this system in his car, which prohibits him from starting the car in the drunken state. If he is alcoholic, the car does not start.
The initiative was announced last month in June and is already part of the report of the Prosecutor General, which, according to them, is a pilot project that will last for a year.
The purpose is the resocialization of the driver, which is why he gets a course for the re-education of traffic behavior.
In addition to the Prosecutor General’s Office, according to experience, the Ministry of Transport and the Foundation of the Technical Institute for the Safety of Automobiles will also participate.
According to statistics, between 30-75% of drivers who were reported to be driving under the influence of alcohol more than once were back at the wheel.
The 'alcolock' would prevent this because it is a system connected to the car, it measures the alcohol content in the exhaled air and prevents car start when the driver has taken alcohol test; or if an alcohol concentration is detected that is higher than allowed.
It costs more than 1 000 euros, the costs are borne by the person who imposes the sanction.
In this context, a study conducted in the U.S. in 2007 showed that cars equipped with these devices prevent up to 65% of rule violations as early as the first year after its introduction.
In Spain, it is estimated that 115 lives could be saved every year.
The measure is limited to administrative sanctions for two reasons: to tackle this behavior before it becomes a crime.
