Napolitano: "Prevention of accidents at work is crucial"
Every day 2,500 accidents occur in Italy, three people die and 27 remain disabled for life.
For 2007, the data of the Inail (Istituto nazionale contro gli infortuni sul lavoro) confirm that the fatal accidents at work were about 1200.
These figures demonstrate the seriousness of a phenomenon that causes almost twice as many deaths as murders.
