Listening to loud music over a longer period of time with portable music devices, such as MP3 players, can lead to permanent hearing damage.
This is reported by the European Commission, which cites the opinion of the EU’s Csrseri (scientific committee on current and recently identified health risks) in a report published today in Brussels.
