These damages can be very limited by resorting to solutions such as the reduction of the volume and the length of the noise exposure.
In its report, the Scientific Committee of the European Union points out that if users of portable music devices only listen to loud music for five hours a week (less than 89 decibels), so that the legal limits that apply to the maximum noise level at the workplace are already exceeded.
