Medicines: never take with fruit juice
Beware of grapefruit, orange and apple juice.
These drinks, which are consumed mainly in summer due to their refreshing quality and vitamin richness, can cause serious health damage when taken at the same time with certain vital medicines, as they can have an extreme effect on the absorption by the body.
David Bailey, professor at the University of Western Ontario in London, repeatedly points out the risk of packaged and fresh fruit juices associated with drug intake. At the 236th meeting of the American Chemical Society in Philadelphia, he once again made an alarm: a glass of apple, orange or grapefruit juice is enough to reduce the intake capacity of certain vital medicines to such an extent that they are virtually eliminated from patients’ health.
Grapefruit juice was already suspected to be responsible for increasing the effects of some drugs such as antibiotics, anti-asthmatic drugs, cardiovascular drugs, anxiolytic and neurological agents, up to toxic levels.
MEDICIALS IN DANGER – The same drug agency had warned doctors and patients about the dangers of this mix in a report two years ago, stressing to pay attention to what is being drunk in conjunction with drugs such as diazepan or metadone.
It’s not just grapefruit – according to experts, orange juice and apple juice also contain substances that can inhibit the drugs.
The list of active ingredients inhibited by the fruit juices is long.
Michele Carruba, director of the Universit<0xC3><0xA0> Statale di Milano, said: "Such results are usually immediately forwarded to the various international manufacturers who are thus free to change consumer information.
Therefore, it is advisable to always read the package leaflet and, if there is still any ambiguity, do not be afraid to ask a pharmacist or doctor," emphasizes the expert of the Ansa agency.
Nobel Prize awarded to Paul Krugman
The Nobel Economic Prize is to the American Paul Krugman for his analysis of trade patterns and the settlement of economic activities.
The 55-year-old Krugman is a Neokeynesian who teaches at the University of Princeton and is known for his regular articles for the New York Times.
Krugman is one of the biggest critics of the Bush administration’s economic and foreign policy.
A few months after the September 11, 2001 attacks, during the days of the Enron collapse, Krugman had claimed in a New York Times editorial that this second event was more crucial to U.S. history than the assassinations.
A prediction that received little polemics in response and was presented to the economist years later, but proves to be completely correct today.
“I am surprised and also shocked at how quickly the memory of the scandals in the context of the collapses of Enron or Worldcom has disappeared from the public eye,” Krugman said in a statement at the end of 2002.
According to Lorenzo Bini Smaghi of the Executive Committee of the European Central Bank, Krugman is an "econom of great value", but also a banaliser with a "very aggressive style that is particularly opposed to the excessive liberalism of the Bush administration."
Open Office, the third version of the "Anti-Microsoft" package appears
The day of the release of OpenOffice.org 3.0 has come; the open source software is gaining an ever-increasing number of users, both at home and in the office, both among freelancers and in public administration, as a free replacement for Microsoft’s Office.
After a year of intensive work by the volunteer developers, which is supervised by SUN Microsystems, the new Open Office now presents itself with some novelties to the audience: in addition to a revised and now more spartanized initial menu, finally a guaranteed compatibility with Apple's operating system Mac OS x is achieved, as well as the support for the new ODF (Open Document Format) 1.2 format, i.e. the latest standard ISO.
Eight against was also the compatibility with Microsoft's Office 2007, whose new formats (.docx, .xlsx, .pptx) can be read by OpenOffice.
Some new features are also interesting, such as those that allow you to reduce the size of PowerPoint presentations, making it easier to send via email, including the ability to import PDF files into graphics editing modules while preserving the original appearance of the page.
In this way, "hybrid" PDF files can also be generated, which extend the typical graphic of the Adobe format with the elements of a table and a word processing system.
Collaboration is one of the most improved elements of the application: tables can now be edited by multiple hands by different users, avoiding conflicts in the event of changes; in the case of the word processing system, each editor is assigned a query to guarantee a better correction procedure.
Some companies are in the process of releasing various features of OpenOffice on the Internet (on the cloud), while the final result will be made public in the coming weeks.
The Italian version is available for download at the following link: http://it.openoffice.org/download/3.0.0/download300.html, so it follows the English version, which has been on the mirrors since Friday.
Apart from Windows and Mac OS, the program is also available for the Linux operating system.
On request, you can have the installation CD sent to your home or office.
While cost-freeness may be an incentive for the program to be distributed in private households, it is also particularly in the business sector where OpenOffice could be a big hit: after all, various public administration and schools have already switched to OpenOffice.
In fact, there is not even a lack of a training offer, which means optimal help for small and medium-sized companies, and thus even opens up business prospects.
OpenOffice consists of five main components: Writer, the Word corresponding text creation program; Calc, the spreadsheet program aimed at supplanting Excel; Impress, for creating presentations like with Powerpoint; Dbase for running databases instead of the more familiar Access; and finally Draw, a graphical module.
The goal for 2008 is to reach 5 million downloads – a goal that can be easily exceeded with already reached 3 million and 600 thousand.
